Benefits:

Dependency Updates: Ensures that projects are always using the latest version of the Parent POM, incorporating any updates or bug fixes.
Stability and Performance: Helps maintain project stability and performance by leveraging the latest features and optimizations.
Risk Reduction: Minimizes the risk of using outdated dependencies, which may contain security vulnerabilities or compatibility issues.
Integration with Maven:

Utilizes Maven commands or plugins to fetch and compare the latest version of the Parent POM.
